{"word":"ἀήθης","slug":"ἀήθης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀήθης</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἦθος'><el>ἦθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unwonted, unusual</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-θως</el>, <i>unexpectedly</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of persons, <i>unused to</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}